race.description: Causley Wholesale Country Boosted Maiden Plate
race.comment: SUNSTAZ (13) closed strongly in her two career runs and has her hoof on the till. Relished the extra trip when she launched late for a narrow third over 1048m at this track. Gets the right tempo and shapes as the main danger. JENNIBELLE (10) Toronado mare from a Savabeel mare on debut for the John Shelton stable. Looked good when winning her latest trial over 940m at this track. Respect. SOL FILIA (12) lightly raced mare resuming. Failed to run the 1200m out when ninth at this track last September. Won her only trial in good style over 1000m and expected to have strengthened over the break. I'M GUESSING (9) returns from a lengthy break. Went out hard from the wide draw with a fading fourth over 1120m at this track last July. Lugging bit goes on and expected to have strengthened this time in.
